# Short description
It seems to be a regression error introduced in flask-restplus 11 as compared to 10.1 regarding examples of nested fields. 

# Background/use case 
We define a basic model A consisting of elementary field types and lists of field types. There are examples on the field level for all fields of model A. 

Then we define a higher level model B that can be seen as a dictionary with 5-10 keys and values of the type that is defined by model A. I want to provide in Swagger documentation an example for the whole model B, instead of using automatically generated concatenated replicas of examples defined in model A. To achieve that we used an `example` parameter of the nested field.

It works correctly with 10.1, but the behavior is broken for 11.0. Basically in definition of model B the `example` parameter on the nested field that is wrapping the model A is ignored in new version

 # Simplified example

What it all boils down to is that the `example` parameter on the nested field declaration is ignored in 11.0.

For a comparison, wrapping the Nested field in List still works consistently between versions - the example on the top level overwriting the examples of the wrapped model. This is the desired behavior from the Nested field


The following definition of the model produces different example values for the example_model in Swagger:


```python
example_model = invoices_namespace.model('example_model',{
    "a_unstable_with_direct_nesting": Nested(
        invoices_namespace.model('badly_linked_model', {
            "some_string_field": fields.String(required=True, example='example_from_field_def')
        }),
        example={
            "some_string_field": "example_from_nesting_wrapper"
        }
    ),
    "b_stable_with_wrapping_nested_in_list": fields.List(Nested(
        invoices_namespace.model('better_linked_model', {
            "some_string_field": fields.String(required=True, example='example_from_field_def')
        })),
        example={
            "some_string_field": "example_from_list_wrapper"
        }
    )
})
```

output from 10.1:

```javascript
[
  {
    "a_unstable_with_direct_nesting": {
      "some_string_field": "example_from_nesting_wrapper"
    },
    "b_stable_with_wrapping_nested_in_list": {
      "some_string_field": "example_from_list_wrapper"
    }
  }
]
```

output from 11.0:

```javascript
[
  {
    "a_unstable_with_direct_nesting": {
      "some_string_field": "example_from_field_def"
    },
    "b_stable_with_wrapping_nested_in_list": {
      "some_string_field": "example_from_list_wrapper"
    }
  }
]
```

