Hi!

Just realized that a check mark lost an alias "ok". It exist as alias for check on the web site, but it doesn't exit in css files any more.

Looks like it's a bug. fa-ok is useful when one decides to quickly switch from glyphicons to fontawesome icons.

Fix. Just add an alias :D
```
.fa-ok:before,
.fa-check:before {
  content: "\f00c";
}
```

