Having access to kernel runtime variables to insert into markdown cells (or other non-code cells/widgets) would be an excellent enhancement for notebooks, particularly when including detailed narrative that describes the results of the code and research. Before posting this, I looked around and found references that lead back to [earlier discussions around this on the ipython repo](https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/2958
), and it seemed like there was interest in getting this implemented.

I searched and didn't see anything already covering this in the jupyter/notebook issue list, so I felt I should raise it here as well, in case key issues like this have not also been migrated along with the code to the new repo. Please see [the original issue](https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/2958
) for a great discussion on this matter, as well as some ideas and implementation estimates.

Since Jupyter now is focused on a more language-neutral approach, I'm sure that complicates the design, but having this functionality, even starting with just Python-based notebooks, would be an attractive addition. I'd like to help move this forward in any way that I can.

